{"type":"message","id":"d66196d2","parentId":"b7c2ec26","timestamp":"2026-05-28T17:38:31.760Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK so the bot_function_explain.md correctly references it as `album_function.md`. The issue is that Spirit's process is looking for `photoalbum_function.md` — this might be a legacy name or a cached reference. Let me check if Spirit's SOUL.md or AGENTS.md has any references.\n\nActually, looking at the error logs more carefully:\n```\nENOENT: no such file or directory, access '/root/.openclaw/workspace-spirit/photoalbum_function.md'\n```\n\nThis error comes from the **tools** when Spirit tried to read `photoalbum_function.md`. This might be something in Spirit's own process/instructions that's cached. \n\nLet me also check if there's an alias or symlink issue. Actually, the issue is probably that Spirit was referencing `photoalbum_function.md` instead of `album_function.md` in its logic. Since I can't modify Spirit's internal behavior directly, I could create a symlink as a workaround.\n\nLet me also get the gateway config to check the allowInsecureAuth.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_EkTFHMsliSaA4fhIzX0u7068","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 创建 symlink 兼容老名称（photoalbum_function.md → album_function.md）\nln -sf album_function.md ~/.openclaw/workspace-spirit/photoalbum_function.md && echo \"symlink created ✅\"\n\n# 查 gateway config\nfind ~/.config -name \"gateway.yaml\" -o -name \"openclaw.yaml\" 2>/dev/null\nls ~/.config/openclaw/ 2>/dev/null"},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"# 创建 symlink 兼容老名称（photoalbum_function.md → album_function.md）\\nln -sf album_function.md ~/.openclaw/workspace-spirit/photoalbum_function.md && echo \\\"symlink created ✅\\\"\\n\\n# 查 gateway config\\nfind ~/.config -name \\\"gateway.yaml\\\" -o -name \\\"openclaw.yaml\\\" 2>/dev/null\\nls ~/.config/openclaw/ 2>/dev/null\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_01_1YBofEjC9Gkxb1LEWnRo286