{"type":"message","id":"fbc6ba7b","parentId":"8135bb0f","timestamp":"2026-05-28T17:41:40.458Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see that the tools config only has `sessions_spawn`, `profile`, and `web`. No `fs` or `image` related restrictions in the config. The image tool restriction is likely a hard-coded security boundary in the OpenClaw platform.\n\nLet me check what directories the image tool can access. The error was \"Local media path is not under an allowed directory\". Earlier I found that copying to workspace-father and reading from there worked. Let me try to copy to workspace-father and use that path.\n\nActually, maybe I should look at what directories ARE allowed for the image tool. The fact that workspace-father worked suggests that each agent's workspace is the allowed directory. So the issue is that Son's workspace-son is not accessible from the Father agent's image tool.\n\nActually wait - looking at the previous flow:\n1. I tried `~/.openclaw/workspace-son/album/images/ALB-20260528-0002.jpg` → Error ✅\n2. I tried `~/ALB-20260528-0002.jpg` → Error ✅ \n3. I tried `~/.openclaw/workspace-father/ALB-20260528-0002.jpg` → Worked! ✅\n\nSo the image tool can only access the current agent's workspace (workspace-father). The solution is:\n- For AI analysis: copy the image to workspace-father first (which I already did manually)\n- This is more of a workflow issue than a config issue\n\nLet me think about whether there's a way to configure allowed paths... Actually, this seems like a security boundary that can't be easily changed through config. The image tool is restricted to the agent's own workspace.\n\nFor now, the workaround is that when we need to analyze an image, we copy it to workspace-father first. This is what I did when I filled in the analysis field.\n\nLet me now move on and also handle the update. Let me present the findings.\n\nActually, the user said \"配置56\" which I think means \"handle both 5 and 6\". Let me handle them.\n\nFor 5: The image path limitation is a platform security boundary. The workaround (copy to workspace-father) works. But let me check if there's a config to add additional allowed directories.\n\nFor 6: Run the update.\n\nLet me handle the update first, it's simpler.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"明白了，56 都安排上。"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_ezw1zEWUFyw7NdIwNFsa2406","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 先更新\nopenclaw update 2>&1","timeout":60},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"# 先更新\\nopenclaw update 2>&1\", \"timeout\": 60}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":336,"output":579,"cacheRead":71552,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":500,"totalTokens":72467,"cost":{"input":0.000047040000000000004,"output":0.00016212,"cacheRead":0.002003456,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0022126159999999997}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779990093504,"responseId":"1dfca58d-bc64-4e7e-8392-318dd42101e8"}}
