{"type":"message","id":"18d8a3c8","parentId":"7903c520","timestamp":"2026-05-28T17:43:48.923Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The original file is gone! Let me check - did the `rm` command I ran earlier remove it through the symlink? Let me check what happened.\n\nActually, looking at my earlier commands:\n```\nrm /root/.openclaw/workspace-father/son-album-images/ALB-20260528-0002.jpg 2>/dev/null\n```\n\nThe symlink `son-album-images` pointed to `/root/.openclaw/workspace-son/album/images`. And since `ALB-20260528-0002.jpg` was already in the target directory, when I ran `rm /root/.openclaw/workspace-father/son-album-images/ALB-20260528-0002.jpg`, it deleted the file in the original location through the symlink.\n\nWait, but then I also ran:\n```\nrm /root/.openclaw/workspace-father/son-album-images 2>/dev/null\n```\n\nThis would have deleted the symlink itself. But now the output says \"symlink exists\"? That's confusing.\n\nWait, looking again at the output:\n```\nsymlink exists\n```\n\nBut the output of `ls -la` for son-album-images says it exists? Let me check if it's a broken symlink now because the real file was deleted.\n\nActually, let me check if the file still exists through the symlink:","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_wJGfLCARPdAlB1ZptETg6204","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 检查文件状态\nls -la /root/.openclaw/workspace-father/son-album-images/\nls -la /root/.openclaw/workspace-father/son-album-images 2>&1\nreadlink /root/.openclaw/workspace-father/son-album-images\nls -la /root/.openclaw/workspace-son/album/images/"},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"# 检查文件状态\\nls -la /root/.openclaw/workspace-father/son-album-images/\\nls -la /root/.openclaw/workspace-father/son-album-images 2>&1\\nreadlink /root/.openclaw/workspace-father/son-album-images\\nls -la /root/.openclaw/workspace-son/album/images/\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flas