{"type":"message","id":"40983772","parentId":"256934b2","timestamp":"2026-05-28T17:44:05.431Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, the file is restored. Now let me address the actual permission issue.\n\nThe user wants me to modify permissions so I (Father) can access Son's workspace files with the image tool. \n\nThe `image` tool checks against an allowed directory list. From the earlier successful tests, I found that:\n- Files in `~/.openclaw/workspace-father/` work\n- Files in `~/.openclaw/workspace-son/` don't work\n\nThe simplest solution would be to either:\n1. Add `workspace-son` as an allowed directory in the config\n2. Change the Father agent config to include `workspace-son` as an additional workspace\n\nLet me check the config schema for this.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"好，图片已经恢复。现在来看怎么把权限搞定——我看看 Father 的 agent 配置能不能把 Son 的 workspace 加进来。"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_659JIZFrHHB7NY7bvH445332","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 -c \"\nimport json\nwith open('/root/.openclaw/openclaw.json', 'r') as f:\n    config = json.load(f)\n\n# 看看工具的配置\ntools = config.get('agents', {}).get('defaults', {}).get('tools', {})\nprint('defaults tools:', json.dumps(tools, indent=2))\n\n# 看看 father 的完整配置\nfor agent in config.get('agents', {}).get('list', []):\n    if agent.get('id') == 'father':\n        print('father:', json.dumps(agent, indent=2))\n\""},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"python3 -c \\\"\\nimport json\\nwith open('/root/.openclaw/openclaw.json', 'r') as f:\\n    config = json.load(f)\\n\\n# 看看工具的配置\\ntools = config.get('agents', {}).get('defaults', {}).get('tools', {})\\nprint('defaults tools:', json.dumps(tools, indent=2))\\n\\n# 看看 father 的完整配置\\nfor agent in config.get('agents', {}).get('list', []):\\n    if agent.get('id') == 'father':\\n        print('father:', json.dumps(agent, indent=2))\\n\\\"\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":211,"output":356,"cacheRead":85376,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":154,"totalTokens":85943,"cost":{"input":0.000029540000000000002,"output":0.00009968000000000001,"cacheRead":0.002390528,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.002519748}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779990241308,"responseId":"2fb63aa4-0d45-4619-8acc-b5f41ab5971c"}}
{"type":"message","id":"6ff6914c","parentId":"40983772","timestamp":"2026-05-28T17:44:05.740Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_659JIZFrHHB7NY7bvH445332","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"defaults tools: {}\nfather: {\n  \"id\": \"father\",\n  \"workspace\": \"/root/.openclaw/workspace-father\",\n  \"subagents\": {\n    \"allowAgents\": [\n      \"*\"\n    ]\n  }\n}"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":140,"aggregated":"defaults tools: {}\nfather: {\n  \"id\": \"father\",\n  \"workspace\": \"/root/.openclaw/workspace-father\",\n  \"subagents\": {\n    \"allowAgents\": [\n      \"*\"\n    ]\n  }\n}","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspace-father"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1779990245739}}
{"type":"message","id":"4c36a6e0","parentId":"6ff6914c","timestamp":"2026-05-28T17:44:09.864Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The workspace is just a single path. There's no \"additional workspaces\" or \"allowed directories\" config option in the agent config for the image tool. The `image` tool is hard-coded to only work with files under the agent's `workspace` directory.\n\nI think the most practical solution is to set up a cron/script that syncs the images between Son and Father workspaces. But that's complex.\n\nActually, a simpler approach: I can use `exec` to copy files before using the image tool. That's what I did earlier when I copied the image to workspace-father and it worked.\n\nBut the user said \"修改权限\" - they want the permission issue fixed. Let me think about this differently.\n\nWhat if I change Father's workspace to something that includes both? Like `/root/.openclaw` - then both workspace-father and workspace-son would be subdirectories.\n\nWait, but that might break other things since all the agents' workspace are under `/root/.openclaw/`. Let me check what the workspace setting affects.\n\nActually, let me read the config docs to understand what `workspace` does for agents.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_MkD6HJ4gLHKungvmCzFJ3126","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/config-agents.md","limit":100},"partialArgs":"{\"path\": \"/usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/config-agents.md\", \"limit\": 100}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":119,"output":314,"cacheRead":85888,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":239,"totalTokens":86321,"cost":{"input":0.00001666,"output":0.00008792000000000001,"cacheRead":0.002404864,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.002509444}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779990245755,"responseId":"e43d39d3-d261-4c0f-93d3-a55572a290a1"}}
{"type":"message","id":"31fe6ee0","parentId":"4c36a6e0","timestamp":"2026-05-28T17:44:10.040Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_MkD6HJ4gLHKungvmCzFJ3126","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nsummary: \"Agent defaults, multi-agent routing, session, messages, and talk config\"\nread_when:\n  - Tuning agent defaults (models, thinking, workspace, heartbeat, media, skills)\n  - Configuring multi-agent routing and bindings\n  - Adjusting session, message delivery, and talk-mode behavior\ntitle: \"Configuration — agents\"\n---\n\nAgent-scoped configuration keys under `agents.*`, `multiAgent.*`, `session.*`,\n`messages.*`, and `talk.*`. For channels, tools, gateway runtime, and other\ntop-level keys, see [Configuration reference](/gateway/configuration-reference).\n\n## Agent defaults\n\n### `agents.defaults.workspace`\n\nDefault: `OPENCLAW_WORKSPACE_DIR` when set, otherwise `~/.openclaw/workspace`.\n\n```json5\n{\n  agents: { defaults: { workspace: \"~/.openclaw/workspace\" } },\n}\n```\n\nAn explicit `agents.defaults.workspace` value takes precedence over\n`OPENCLAW_WORKSPACE_DIR`. Use the environment variable to point default agents\nat a mounted workspace when you do not want to write that path into config.\n\n### `agents.defaults.repoRoot`\n\nOptional repository root shown in the system prompt's Runtime line. If unset, OpenClaw auto-detects by walking upward from the workspace.\n\n```json5\n{\n  agents: { defaults: { repoRoot: \"~/Projects/openclaw\" } },\n}\n```\n\n### `agents.defaults.skills`\n\nOptional default skill allowlist for agents that do not set\n`agents.list[].skills`.\n\n```json5\n{\n  agents: {\n    defaults: { skills: [\"github\", \"weather\"] },\n    list: [\n      { id: \"writer\" }, // inherits github, weather\n      { id: \"docs\", skills: [\"docs-search\"] }, // replaces defaults\n      { id: \"locked-down\", skills: [] }, // no skills\n    ],\n  },\n}\n```\n\n- Omit `agents.defaults.skills` for unrestricted skills by default.\n- Omit `agents.list[].skills` to inherit the defaults.\n- Set `agents.list[].skills: []` for no skills.\n- A non-empty `agents.list[].skills` list is the final set for that agent; it\n  does not merge with defaults.\n\n### `agents.defaults.skipBootstrap`\n\nDisables automatic creation of workspace bootstrap files (`AGENTS.md`, `SOUL.md`, `TOOLS.md`, `IDENTITY.md`, `USER.md`, `HEARTBEAT.md`, `BOOTSTRAP.md`).\n\n```json5\n{\n  agents: { defaults: { skipBootstrap: true } },\n}\n```\n\n### `agents.defaults.skipOptionalBootstrapFiles`\n\nSkips creation of selected optional workspace files while still writing required bootstrap files. Valid values: `SOUL.md`, `USER.md`, `HEARTBEAT.md`, and `IDENTITY.md`.\n\n```json5\n{\n  agents: {\n    defaults: {\n      skipOptionalBootstrapFiles: [\"SOUL.md\", \"USER.md\"],\n    },\n  },\n}\n```\n\n### `agents.defaults.contextInjection`\n\nControls when workspace bootstrap files are injected into the system prompt. Default: `\"always\"`.\n\n- `\"continuation-skip\"`: safe continuation turns (after a completed assistant response) skip workspace bootstrap re-injection, reducing prompt size. Heartbeat runs and post-compaction retries still rebuild context.\n- `\"never\"`: disable workspace bootstrap and context-file injection on every turn. Use this only for agents that fully own their prompt lifecycle (custom context engines, native runtimes that build their own context, or specialized bootstrap-free workflows). Heartbeat and compaction-recovery turns also skip injection.\n\n```json5\n{\n  agents: { defaults: { contextInjection: \"continuation-skip\" } },\n}\n```\n\n\n[1439 more lines in file. Use offset=101 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1779990250039}}
{"type":"message","id":"3ebd0b8c","parentId":"31fe6ee0","timestamp":"2026-05-28T17:44:17.576Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The workspace is a single directory setting for each agent. Nothing about multi-workspace or additional allowed directories for the image tool.\n\nLet me think about a simpler approach. The `image` tool checks if the file path starts with the agent's workspace directory. What if I change Father's workspace to `/root/.openclaw`? Then both `workspace-father/` and `workspace-son/` would be subdirectories of the workspace, and the image tool would likely allow access.\n\nBut wait - this might cause other issues since the workspace is used for other purposes too (file reads/writes, tool operations, etc.).\n\nActually, let me just test this approach. The workspace setting is just used for:\n1. Bootstrap file creation\n2. Tool path validation\n3. Default working directory for exec\n\nIf I change it to `/root/.openclaw`, all the files would still be accessible. Let me update it.\n\nWait, but this might be risky. Let me think of a safer approach.\n\nActually, the most practical approach given the constraints might be to:\n1. Set up a bind mount or symlink from Son's images dir to Father's workspace\n2. But we saw that symlinks don't work (image tool resolves the real path)\n\nAnother option: create a dedicated shared directory under workspace-father and set up automatic sync.\n\nActually, the simplest approach could be to change Father's workspace to `/root/.openclaw`. The bootstrap files would still be created properly since they're relative to the workspace. Let me check what files Father has.\n\nHmm, but `workspace-father/AGENTS.md` etc are in the subdirectory. If the workspace is set to `/root/.openclaw`, the system prompt would say workspace is `/root/.openclaw`, and my AGENTS.md etc would need to be at that level, not in the subdirectory.\n\nActually no - the agent workspace is where the agent-specific files live. Changing it to `/root/.openclaw` would mean the agent looks for AGENTS.md etc directly at that level, not in workspace-father. I'd need to move or relink files.\n\nThat's too invasive. Let me think of another approach.\n\nWhat about adding `tools.fs.workspaceOnly: false` or something similar? Let me check if there's a config for the image tool specifically.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_J6rg1pJJc7iLr58nYStw1441","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 看看配置参考文档中关于 tools 和 image 的配置\ngrep -r \"image\\|media.*path\\|workspaceOnly\\|allowedDir\" /usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/ --include=\"*.md\" -l 2>/dev/null"},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"# 看看配置参考文档中关于 tools 和 image 的配置\\ngrep -r \\\"image\\\\|media.*path\\\\|workspaceOnly\\\\|allowedDir\\\" /usr/local/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/gateway/ --include=\\\"*.md\\\" -l 2>/dev/null\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":891,"output":593,"cacheRead":86272,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":490,"totalTokens":87756,"cost":{"input":0.00012474,"output":0.00016604,"cacheRead":0.0024156159999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.002706396}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779990250059,"responseId":"d7ab271c-5675-41fc-92f2-95af2826bd53"}}
