{"type":"message","id":"49ab6c53","parentId":"1002520a","timestamp":"2026-05-28T17:44:47.072Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Still not working. The `tools.fs.workspaceOnly=false` doesn't affect the `image` tool's path restriction. The `image` tool has its own hard-coded security check.\n\nSince the user said \"分析image不是都应该交给son吗\" - they're right, image analysis should be handled by Son anyway. Son's workspace is workspace-son, and the image tool should work fine from Son's context.\n\nSo the right answer to \"修改权限\" is not about giving Father access to Son's files - it's about acknowledging that Father should delegate image analysis to Son, and making sure Son has the ability to do it (which it already does).\n\nLet me revert the `workspaceOnly` change since it's not the fix, and tell the user what I found.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"`tools.fs.workspaceOnly` 不控制 image 工具——它只管 `read/write/edit`。image 工具有自己的硬编码安全策略，每个 agent 只能看自己的 workspace。\n\n所以权限修正方案其实是另一条路——你说得对，**看图分析本来就是仔仔的活**。\n\n以后流程改进：\n\n```\n需要图片分析\n  ├─ 我（Faye）：调用 image 工具 → 如果是 workspace-father 下的图，直接读\n  └─ 我（Faye）：如果是 Son 那边存的图\n       → spawn 仔仔，让它用 qwen-vl 读自己 workspace 下的图分析\n       → 仔仔返回分析结果 → 我转发\n```\n\n这样不需要改任何权限，仔仔的 qwen-vl 本来就能读自己的图。刚才我手伸太长自己调用 image 才是问题。\n\n要不要我把 config 里刚才加的 `tools.fs.workspaceOnly: false` 改回来？那个本来就不起作用。"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":106,"output":376,"cacheRead":92800,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":162,"totalTokens":93282,"cost":{"input":0.00001484,"output":0.00010528000000000001,"cacheRead":0.0025984,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00271852}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1779990281562,"responseId":"bf91e92b-089e-45d5-a842-5bfd786a55d2"}}
