{"type":"message","id":"52f1b5c1","parentId":"969b8f7b","timestamp":"2026-05-28T17:58:53.261Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to restructure the album storage to use user-specific subdirectories. Let me plan this:\n\n1. Create `album/images/{sender_id}/` subdirectories\n2. Move existing images into their respective user subdirectories\n3. Update the database to store the correct relative path or filename\n4. Update Spirit's function definition to use the new path structure\n5. Make sure the flow from Spirit → Son reflects the new structure\n\nLet me do this step by step:\n\n1. First, move existing images\n2. Update the database (the filename column needs to be updated or we store full path)\n3. Update Spirit's album_function.md to reference the new directory structure\n4. Update the album data JSON files in Spirit's directory\n\nWait, let me think about the architecture more carefully. Currently:\n- Spirit has `album/data/*.json` - legacy JSON storage\n- Son has `album/album.db` - SQLite database\n- Both have `album/images/` with flat files\n\nThe user wants:\n- `album/images/{sender_id}/` structure\n\nFor the database, the `filename` field should probably store just the filename still (like `ALB-20260528-0002.jpg`), and the system should know to look in `images/{sender_id}/` subdirectory. Or we could store the full relative path.\n\nLet me go with: `filename` stores just the base filename, and the system constructs the path as `images/{sender_id}/{filename}`.\n\nLet me proceed with the restructuring.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"好，开整。先把现有数据结构调整过来，然后改 Spirit 的功能定义。"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_jwTQHNQ8plrIkqIh0noY0984","name":"update_plan","arguments":{"plan":[{"step":"创建用户子目录 + 迁移图片","status":"in_progress"},{"step":"更新数据库路径记录","status":"pending"},{"step":"更新 Spirit 的 album_function.md 路径逻辑","status":"pending"},{"step":"清理 Spirit 旧 JSON 存储的数据路径","status":"pending"}],