{"type":"message","id":"bdfa5572","parentId":"c836f476","timestamp":"2026-05-28T18:24:19.890Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The TERM is set to \"dumb\" which means the terminal doesn't support the full TUI features. When you run `openclaw tui` from an SSH session, the TERM variable needs to be set to something like `xterm-256color` or `xterm` for the TUI to work properly.\n\nAlso, the \"dumb\" terminal means the TUI might not render properly or might crash.\n\nBut wait - the user said they got errors. Let me ask them what the actual error message was.\n\nActually, another common issue: the environment variables might not be set right when SSH-ing in. Or the user might be trying to run it in a way that doesn't work.\n\nLet me check if there's a specific issue by running the TUI command and capturing the error.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"大概率是终端环境问题——你的 SSH 客户端 TERM 是 `dumb`，TUI 界面依赖的终端能力它没有。\n\n你 SSH 的时候加个 `-t` 参数试试：\n\n```bash\nssh -t root@你的服务器IP\nopenclaw tui\n```\n\n或者你在 SSH 客户端里确认一下终端类型设置（比如用 MobaXterm、Xshell 的话，看下终端仿真是不是设成了 xterm）。\n\n你之前报的具体错误信息是什么？方便贴一下吗？🚬"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":69,"output":279,"cacheRead":116608,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":166,"totalTokens":116956,"cost":{"input":0.00000966,"output":0.00007812,"cacheRead":0.003265024,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.003352804}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1779992654637,"responseId":"f3fbeb7c-db4c-4583-9c55-fa99b9d35fd3"}}
