{"type":"message","id":"11f7866c","parentId":"7f599b59","timestamp":"2026-05-28T18:25:03.907Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see the actual error. The TUI is actually working and connecting to the gateway, but it's hitting a **pairing/authorization** issue. \n\nThe gateway is asking for device pairing approval. The TUI is connecting from a device that hasn't been approved yet. The user needs to:\n\n1. Run `openclaw devices list` on the server\n2. Find the requestId: `332d3b0b-f223-48ce-a639-e4cd374e1` \n3. Approve it\n\nBut wait - the user is asking ME (running on the server) to fix this so they can use TUI. Since I'm running as the father agent on the same server, I can approve the pairing request for them.\n\nLet me check the devices list and approve the pending pairing request.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"看到报错了——不是 TUI 崩了，是网关在要求**设备配对授权**。\n\n我来处理。"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_x4I7ywa1KOxvY8iNhQm77263","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw devices list 2>&1"},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"openclaw devices list 2>&1\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":1393,"output":245,"cacheRead":115712,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":171,"totalTokens":117350,"cost":{"input":0.00019502,"output":0.0000686,"cacheRead":0.003239936,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.003503556}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779992699206,"responseId":"7fbbaf40-1a94-40eb-a304-913e6db86f70"}}
